OL,3,CFamilies 'choosing between feeding
OL,4,Cchildren and buying school uniform'
OL,6,FIn a bid to ease the financial
OL,7,Fhardship facing some low-income
OL,8,Ffamilies across the Channel Islands,
OL,9,Fcharities and businesses are running
OL,10,Finitiatives to help parents offset the
OL,11,Fcosts.
OL,13,FAutism Jersey partners with Marks and
OL,14,FSpencer to offer a 10% voucher off new
OL,15,Funiforms when parents donate old ones
OL,16,Fto the charity's shop.
OL,18,FThere are other means of support that
OL,19,Ffamilies can access, such as speaking
OL,20,Fwith the Education Welfare Officer at
OL,21,Ftheir child's school.
